Concept: 
Crowley makes examples of his plants that don't do well and all, but he's really just transfering them to like a...
body:
Concept:

Crowley makes examples of his plants that don’t do well and all, but he’s really just transfering them to like a greenhouse because they’re more delicate and he can take gentler care of them there.

Aziraphale follows him one day hoping to save a poor plant but finds it being transferred by a cooing Crowley. He just finds it adorably endearing and just a wee bit hilarious.

summary:
"Aziraphale and Crowley are in love," I say into the mic. 
The crowd boos. I begin to walk off the stage in shame when a voice...
body:
“Aziraphale and Crowley are in love,” I say into the mic.

The crowd boos. I begin to walk off the stage in shame when a voice speaks, silencing everybody.

“She’s right.” It says. I look for the owner of the voice and there in the 3rd row I see him: Michael Sheen himself.
